The article is a statement from the leaders of several countries, including Australia, Canada, Japan, and the United States, regarding the progress made in the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP) negotiations. The leaders express their satisfaction with the narrowing of gaps in the legal text of the agreement and the intensification of negotiations to open up markets and bring the TPP to a conclusion. They emphasize the importance of concluding the agreement quickly to allow businesses, workers, farmers, and consumers to benefit from it. The leaders also highlight their commitment to an ambitious, comprehensive, high-standard, and balanced agreement that promotes economic growth, job creation, and sustainable development. They express their openness to including other regional partners in the TPP if they adopt its high standards. The leaders stress the importance of continued engagement and input from stakeholders as the negotiations progress.